===Etymology===
From [[French]] + [[horn]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[French]] [[horn]]}}

#{{musici}} The American name for a [[coiled]] [[brass]] [[musical instrument]] derived from the French [[hunting horn]], having rotary [[valves]].

====Synonyms====
*[[Viennese horn]] 

====See Also====
*[[double horn]]
*[[trumpet]]

<!--encyclopedic: the user can find this sort of information in the Wikipedia entry.  It originally had no valves and was made twice as long as a trumpet of similar tonal range so that more overtones could be employed.  The right hand was inserted into the bell to "[[bend]]" the [[pitch]] and match the tone needed.  A modern French horn has [[valves]] and is often made as two horns in one with different [[tonal]] [[ranges]] (a "double" horn).  The hand is still used for fine tuning and to produce a special muted sound (a hand "stop").-->

